activators use the slmgr commands.  They are not activation bypasses, they are just frontends for legit activation methods.  They get passed to microsoft constantly and blacklisted.  You are better off finding a non-blacklisted key and running commands such as:

slmgr /upk
slmgr /ipk XKY4K-2NRWR-8F6P2-448RF-CRYQH
slmgr -skms kms.creighton.edu
slmgr -ato

run as admin command prompt (winkey+x then admin prompt) press enter after every command and then wait a few seconds.

I wouldn't bother installing media center versions until someone comes up with a crack.  the only way to activate them is by installing pro, then doing the microsoft dialup with a media center upgrade key.  You can then save the key with Advanced Tokens Manager Beta 3 or later for installs to media center. For that, you need to run slmgr /upk first, then click the restore.
